race.description: Raine & Horne Hobart & Kingborough Rentals Maiden
race.comment: Competitive. TIMELY NEEDS (3) was unplaced on debut then improved beaten 2 lengths over 1220m at Launceston. The longer sprint suits and the top hoop stays aboard. Well placed and gets his chance to break through. TASSIE POWER (2) was beaten by a similar margin first up. He has more to give and the step up in trip is in his favour. Maps well and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. ALPINE COWGIRL (4) continues to race well without breaking through. Good enough at best and can't be ruled out. SEDITIOUS AWARD (8) is an improver with a 3kg claim drawn wide. Will be around the mark with average luck.
